09/05/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Senior police representatives from Albania, Macedonia and Montenegro met in Tirana on Tuesday (May 8th) to discuss regional police co-operation and strengthening the fight against organised crime.
In particular, they discussed collaboration during the upcoming summer tourist season.
In other news Tuesday, Montenegrin Defence Minister Boro Vucinic met with a delegation from EUFOR.
They discussed how Podgorica's experience with destroying surplus armaments and explosives could be useful to BiH.
(Vijesti - 09/05/07;
RTCG - 08/05/07)
